Hi all, I will make a try too... Web accessibility means that everyone can use the functions of a web site; 
* regardless of disability and the use of assitive technology; * regardless of the operating system and the user agent (browser, PDA, WAP, TV) that is used. 
Web accessibility includes the content of a web site, the authoring tools of web design and the user agents to explore the web. 
In this definition main stream and special use is included (some people like that a lot). 
I know that some of you do have a problem with the wording *everyone can use...*, but what about the Tim Berners-Lee slogan? 
(see below) 
"The power of the Web is in its universality. 
Access by everyone regardless of disability is an essential aspect." 
Tim Berners-Lee, W3C Director and inventor of the World Wide Web Regards, 
